article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 73, Fordham 68
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Donavan Monroe scored 15 points, and Tony White and Andrew Goudelock each added 12 to help Charleston beat Fordham 73-68 on Saturday. Marcus Stout had 19 points for Fordman, and Mike Moore added 17. After Monroe's three-point play gave the Cougars (2-3) a 66-53 advantage with 3:58 remaining, Fordham (2-3) reeled off 10 straight points to cut it to 66-63 with 1:09 to go. Stout led the surge with a pair of layups. Charleston scored its final seven points from the foul line, two each by Monroe, Dunston Scott and Marcus Hammond, to seal the victory.
